ustomer’s\n\nhighest\n\ndistribution\n\ndemand\n\nregardless\n\nwhen\n\nthat\n\ndemand\n\noccurs.'>\n\nTCPA\n\ndoes\n\nnot\n\ninherently\n\ndisagree\n\nwith\n\nStaff’s\n\nposition\n\non\n\nthe\n\nappropriateness\n\nof\n\nthe\n\nNCP\n\nmethod\n\nfor\n\nallocating\n\ndistribution\n\ncosts.\n\nRather,\n\nTCPA\n\nbelieves\n\nthat\n\nthe\n\nevidence\n\ndemonstrates\n\nthat\n\ntransmission\n\ncosts\n\nare\n\nalso\n\nincurred\n\nfor\n\nreasons\n\nalmost\n\nentirely\n\ndivorced\n\nfrom\n\n4CP\n\ndemand.\n\nTherefore,\n\nan\n\nNCP\n\nmethod\n\nof\n\nallocation\n\nis\n\nequally\n\nas\n\nappropriate\n\nfor\n\ntransmission\n\ncosts\n\nas\n\ndistribution\n\ncosts.\n\nA.\n\nPURA\n\nand\n\nthe\n\nCommission’s\n\nRules\n\ndo\n\nnot\n\nRequire\n\n4CP\n\nAllocation\n\nto\n\nRetail\n\nCustomers\n\nTCPA\n\nand\n\nCenterPoint\n\nagree\n\nthat\n\nStaff’s\n\nasserted\n\nposition\n\nthat\n\na\n\n4CP\n\nallocation\n\nmethod\n\nfor\n\nretail\n\ncustomers\n\nis\n\nrequired\n\nby\n\nPURA\n\nand\n\nthe\n\nCommission’s\n\nRules\n\nis\n\nfundamentally\n\nincorrect.\n\nStaff\n\nwitness\n\nWilliam\n\nAbbott\n\ntestified\n\nthat\n\nthe\n\n“Commission\n\nhas\n\ndetermined\n\nthat\n\n[4CP]\n\nis\n\nthe\n\nbasis\n\nby\n\nwhich\n\ntransmission\n\ncosts\n\nshould\n\nbe\n\nallocated\n\nto\n\nand\n\ncollected\n\nfrom\n\ncustomers”\n\nand\n\nthat\n\nPURA\n\n§\n\n35.004(d)\n\nand\n\n16\n\nTAC\n\n§\n\n192.(b)(1)\n\nmandate\n\nuse\n\nof\n\nthe\n\n4CP\n\n13\n\nmethod\n\nfor\n\ntransmission\n\ncost\n\nallocation\n\nto\n\nretail\n\ncustomers.””\n\nThis\n\nposition\n\nwas\n\nrefuted\n\nby\n\nCenterPoint\n\nwitness\n\nMatt\n\nTroxle,\n\nwho\n\ntestified:\n\n“[16\n\nTAC\n\n§\n\n192]\n\nis\n\nthe\n\nwholesale\n\ntransmission\n\nrule.\n\nWholesale\n\ntransmission\n\ncosts,\n\nessentially,\n\ngo\n\ninto\n\nthe\n\nERCOT\n\nnet\n\nwholesale\n\npayment\n\nmefrics,\n\nand\n\nthen\n\nthey\n\nget\n\nspread\n\nout\n\nto\n\nthe\n\nother\n\ndistribution\n\nservice\n\nproviders\n\nin\n\nERCOT.\n\nWhereas\n\nwhen\n\nyou’re\n\ntalking\n\nabout\n\nallocation\n\nto\n\nthe\n\ncustomer\n\nclasses,\n\n[that’s]\n\na\n\nretail\n\nissue,\n\nnot\n\na\n\nwholesale\n\nissue.”",
