      "text": "​Wholesale transmission service\n\nSkip to main content Skip to navigation Skip to secondary navigation Skip to footer Skip to search\n\nThe browser you are using is out of date and will soon be unsupported. Please update to the latest version or view our site in another browser.\n\nPage Content\n\n​​​​Wholesale Transmission Service\n\nCenterPoint Energy provides open access to CenterPoint Energy's transmission system to eligible customers (as defined in Public Utility Commission of Texas [PUCT] Substantive Rule 25.5 in accordance with PUCT Substantive Rules 25.191-25.204 under the following tariffs approved by the PUCT and/or FERC:\n\n### Wholesale Transmission Service (WTS-TCOS)​\n\nTransmission service within the Electric Reliability Council of Texas (ERCOT) is provided under the Substantive Rules of the PUCT, CenterPoint Energy's Tariff Rate Schedule WTS, and ERCOT Protocols.\n\n### ​Addresses for use by Transmission Service Providers​​\n\nFor billing purposes:\n\nAccounts Payable CenterPoint Energy P.O. Box 1374 ​ Houston, Texas 77251-1374\n\nNOTE: The body of the invoice must prominently display the following alphanumeric characters: WF012243\n\nFor remittance by check:\n\nRemittance Department CenterPoint Energy P.O. Box 1700 Houston, Texas 77251-1700\n\n### To, From and Over Service (TFO)​​\n\nTransmission service for power exported from ERCOT over high voltage direct current (HVDC) ties is provided under the Substantive Rules of the PUCT, CenterPoint Energy's Tariff for Transmission Service To, From and Over Certain Interconnections, and ERCOT Protocols.",
