      "text": "Skip to content\n\nEnergy Market Insights Powered by Earth Etch\n\nSubscribe\n\nSign In\n\nOpen menu\n\n×\n\nSubscribe\n\nEnergize\n\n# Market Alerts\n\n## TX – CNP Implementation of Distribution Cost Recovery Factor (DCRF) Rates Effective December 7, 2025\n\nPublished October 24, 2025\n\nCategory: Texas\n\nRelated Categories: Electric, Market Alert, Rate Change, Utility\n\nNotice Date: October 23, 2025\nNotice Type: Informational\n\nShort Description: CenterPoint Energy Houston Electric, LLC’s Distribution Cost Recovery Factor (DCRF) Rates will be effective December 7, 2025.\n\nIntended Audience: Competitive Retailers\nDay Affected: December 7, 2025\n\nLong Description: On August 15, 2025, CenterPoint Energy Houston Electric, LLC (“CenterPoint Houston”) filed, Docket No. 58537, with the Public Utility Commission of Texas (“Commission”) an Application for Approval to Amend its Distribution Cost Recovery Factor (“DCRF”) pursuant to 16 TEX. ADMIN. CODE (“TAC”) §25.243. On October 23, 2025, the presiding officer in this proceeding issued a Final Order consistent with the rates shown below, effective for usage on and after December 7, 2025.\n\nThe DCRF is an interim rate adjustment allowed by Texas statute that permits electric utilities to implement new rates to account for changes in distribution invested capital without filing a full rate case.\n\nThe Rider DCRF rates will include the following charges on bills rendered to REPs:\n\n| Rate Class | DCRF Charge Effective December 7, 2025 | Billing Units |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| Residential Service | $ 0.003198 | per kWh |\n| Secondary Service Less Than or Equal to 10 kVA | $ 0.002912 | per kWh |\n| Secondary Service Greater Than 10 kVA | $ 0.499241 | per Billing kVA |\n| Primary Service and Wholesale Distribution Service | $ 0.270146 | per Billing kVA |\n| Transmission Service | $ 0.006994 | per 4CP kVA |\n| Lighting Services | $ 0.052811 | per kWh |\n\nPersons with questions or who want more information